They just met their initial fundraising goal and are having a community forum next Tuesday for a building project at SE 82nd/Division. There are 48 units of affordable housing planned and a 5,000 sq/ft cultural center . If you live in the neighborhood or are generally interested, here are the details for the forum: <https://apano.salsalabs.org/jamsforum/index.html>

attachments.title: Furniture Store Redevelopment Community Forum
attachments.text: March 7: Learn more about our plans and progress for building 48 units of affordable housing, a public plaza, cultural center and nonprofit offices at the corner of 82nd & SE Division in the Jade District, where the discount furniture store resides.
